runs.comm: around the wicket, leg stump, clipped out to deep midwicket
length on the stumps, forward and blocked up the wicket
swept from outside off but finds square leg, sharp save
too short and cut away through cover point
swept from middle and leg and this time gets it backward of square, well struck
fuller length and clipped out to deep midwicket
leg stump line and Lumb lets it hit his thigh pad, very strange
full length, bit of inswing onto the stumps, Lumb punches up to mid-off
shorter length, strikes the body as Lumb looks to play to leg
too short and wide and Lumb slaps it over point, reasonably well struck
little short again and Lumb powers a pull wide of mid-on, a short-arm bash from just outside off
full and wide, driven at but misses
good length sliding across off stump, Hales drives and a fumble at point gives them a single
full and some swing, pushed at outside off and gets a thick inside edge to midwicket
excellent full length on off stump, dug out towards mid-on and they race a single
full length and firmly driven, gets a thick outside edge to gully and Maxwell puts it down that is a simple chance, straight to him
full and some inswing into the pads, Hales misses trying to flick to leg
full length just outside off, Hales swings it wide of mid-on, the 39-year-old gives chase and could have done much better there, his slide is not in time
down the wicket and swings at a length ball just outside off, gets a toe-end that runs to slip in the end

full length on off stump, Lumb tries to heave over the leg side but puts it straight up in the air and mid-on takes a solid catch. Lively from Lumb but he's totally miscued that trying to pick a ball up over the leg side
short of a length, pulled hard and beats deep-square leg, well timed
fuller length, worked with the angle wide of short long leg but not enough on it for any more than a couple
full length outside off, Hales scythes it to cover point
down the track and a wild swing towards the leg side misses
full length a foot wide of off stump, Wright drives and misses completely

full length wide of off stump again, Wright smashes it into the off side and Hodge takes a blinding catch diving down to his right, fabulous take and Wright fails again, nailed the stroke but a foot off the ground was enough for Hodge
too wide and Root begins perfectly with a nice cut stroke through point
cover drive this time and four more with decent timing again, too wide from Starc
full toss outside off now but Root seems so surprised by it he misses completely and Starc gets away with one
tighter line, full length, nudged up to mid-on
length ball wide of off stump, driven in the air up and over cover point
much better, tight off stump line, just back of a length, blocked up the wicket
fuller and straighter, Hales flicks around the corner but can only find short long leg

full on the stumps, Hales aims a big swing towards the leg side and gets a huge top edge that swirls down to third man and Starc holds the chance very well. That hung in the air for a long time but Starc steadied himself just inside the boundary and took it down to his left with two hands
length on leg stump, clipped through square leg and they run hard for two
too wide and Root slaps it wide of third man, good start for him
reverse sweep first ball and he nails it past short third man, super timing from off stump
length on middle and leg, tickled down the leg side and short long leg comes to his left to field, can't prevent the single though
stays around the wicket, full on off stump, clipped down to long-off
full length just outside off, driven down to long-off
length outside off, a cross-bat slap to extra cover

the same stroke but this time they take on extra-cover and a direct hit has Morgan struggling diving into the striker's end. His bat is well over the line but it's bounced in the air, are his gloves back in time? I don't think they are and indeed he's gone. Very unlucky that is for Morgan, the bat bounced up and all the way to the top of the handle was in the air as he crossed the whitewash. Top work from Hodge having run to his left
tossed onto leg stump, Root forward to block
spins well wide of off stump and called so as Root's cut misses, sharp turn there
touch shorter, Root right back to pull and finds deep-midwicket
fuller just outside off, driven down to long-off
floated up outside off, driven firmly to extra cover
forward and driven down to long-off
full length and Buttler slaps it down to long-off
touch short on leg stump, clipped wide of the leg side 45 for an easy single
back of a length just outside off, Root back to pull on the bounce to long-on

forward pushing into midwicket and they charge back for the second, Maxwell charges in and returns a super throw and Root has to dive into the non-striker's end and it short of his ground! What superb fielding. Looked for all money that an easy two was on but Maxwell covered the ground so quickly, dived to field and threw almost in one motion, right on target and White dashed the stumps down
back foot punch out to deep cover
back foot punch this time down to long-off
back and clipped to Maxwell again at deep-midwicket, no though of a second this time
driven on the up to deep cover with the turn
forward just blocking on the stumps
back and trying to force into the off side, bit of bounce beats the stroke
full and well wide of off stump, Bopara reaches out for it and slaps to deep cover
full length just outside off, driven hard to long-off
full toss on leg stump, swept hard to deep-square leg
dropped short, Bopara swivels and hoicks one through the leg side
tossed up on the stumps, comes forward and pushes one down the ground
floated up and worked off the legs into a gap at midwicket
there's Buttler's power, he rocks back and smashes a muscular pull out in front of deep midwicket for four
pushed through a little quicker, outside off and edged past Wade trying to cut, short third man cleans up
full, tapped into the leg side, no run
drops short, Buttler stays back and nudges a couple behind square on the leg side
length ball outside off, driven on the up towards mid-off
shot! That's a crunching blow from Buttler, whipping the hands through a pull shot and sends the ball rocketing to deep midwicket, the sweeper had no chance
comes forward, forces the ball back down the ground, past midwicket
fuller, on off stump, wristy little flick to square leg from Bopara
pitched up outside the line, Buttler gives a cover drive some billy-oh but Bailey takes it on the bounce

lovely delivery, beats Bopara in the flight as he gropes forward and there's a stumping appeal, nicely done by Wade but I think Bopara is going to survive this one (you can reverse those two clauses for Adelaide last weekend). Yep, replays confirm he just got his toe back
angled in and sliding down the leg side - wide

on the stumps, Bopara reaches for the slog-sweep... and he's picked out deep midwicket! Good bit of bowling from Muirhead again, think it dipped on Bopara, who wasn't able to control the shot, sent it flat and at a comfortable height to the man
length ball turning away outside off, patted behind square for a couple
gets on the front foot and pushes into the covers
goes back and cuts again, more firmly this time, but an excellent diving stop on the rope prevents four
beaten past the outside edge as Buttler stayed back and tried to run one off the face
back of a length, cracked off the back foot through the covers for a single
short again, tapped towards point from the crease
comes forward, tries to drive a length ball, Hazlewood fields in his follow through
slings this down the leg side, that'll be a wide
short and outside off, Buttler can't get the ball away through backward point
short, on the stumps, tucks the batsman up and it's blocked back down the track
bit of width, the ball zips off a length and past the bat as Buttler has a big ole mow and misses
floated up outside off, Bresnan opens the face and steers one to backward point
tossed up, reverses the hands and swats the ball hard but straight to point
flatter and quicker, as Buttler opens the shoulders and tries to hit over mid-on, fails to connect properly
pushed through outside off, pushed into the covers
goes for the reverse sweep again, picks out point and this time they scamper one
tossed up on middle and off, straightens a touch, Bresnan shows it a straight bat
pitched up, shaping in and that's out! Buttler didn't move his feet, think Coulter-Nile just cut his fingers over the ball and it was a pretty straight forward decision
stays back and pushes a shortish ball to point
works one into the midwicket area
Bresnan slogs hard across the line, gets a top edge but it drops tantalisingly short of long-on running in
Broad waits and cuts a length ball out towards deep point
pitched up, outside the line of off, driven on the front foot straight to mid-off
Broad backs to leg, Starc and Wade follow him and a short-of-a-length ball clips the thigh pad, beats Wade to his left and runs to the boundary - hundred up for England now
shortish, on the stumps, Broad steps away and slaps one over gully
dug in short and this flies through to Wades as Bresnan swings and misses
good length, around off stump, Bresnan heaves and inside edge into his front pad
gets on the front foot and plays a classical front-foot drive straight to cover - another dot
something a bit more agricultural now, hacks at a length ball in the channel and carves a single to third man
slower ball from Coulter-Nile, on off stump, Bresnan miscues a drive to the edge of the off-side ring
goes for the yorker, lines this one up and drives crisply down the ground for one to long-on
bangs this into the deck halfway down and Broad happily hooks towards deep square leg, just a yard or two short of the rope
picks up a couple more from the short delivery, pulled higher this time but it plops safely into the outfield at deep midwicket
backs away, throws the hands at a wide-ish short ball, slices one to third man
now Bresnan clears the front foot and clubs to leg, doesn't quite get hold of it but that's a couple more
Starc follows Broad as he goes to leg, hit on the pad as he swings across the line
full and tailing in towards off stump, Broad swings hard and misses completely
another swing and a miss, this one perilously close to off stump, Starc giving nothing away
manages to connect this time, bundles a single into the leg side
goes full and wide of the stumps, Bresnan jams the bat down and squeezes one into the off side
full again and shaping back on middle and leg, Broad manages to inside edge the ball to deep backward square but Maxwell's arm keeps them to one
Broad steps away, this is fired wide of the wicket in respone - too wide for the umpire
carted high out towards long-off, a huge top edge from Broad, it lands beyond the fielder, though, just inside the rope, and they survive run-out chances at both ends to get back for three
bosh! Finally a clean connection from Bresnan, who hits a full toss out of the screws and down the ground to bisect long-on and long-off
fires this to leg as the batsman makes room, turned behind square

Broad is swinging like kid in a playground, another skier flies out towards deep backward point, it bounces towards the rope where Maxwell swoops on it like condor, collect and tosses the ball to a team-mate superbly to prevent a boundary

bowled him, via his legs! Bresnan tried to get cute, stepping outside off and attempting to dab the ball fine on the leg side, failed to connect with the bat and it clipped his back leg before ricocheting into the stumps
timber! Hazlewood has four! Full and straight does for Tredwell, who tried to launch his first ball down the ground and missed it completely. The stumps are a mess and so is this England innings
